Governor Muhammad Inuwa Yahaya of Gombe State has approved the use of Kaltungo Model School as a temporary site for the take-off of Federal Polytechnic, Kaltungo in the state. He said this yesterday when recieving a Federal Government’s Committee on the take-off of the Federal Polytechnic approved by President Muhammadu Buhari. The governor said apart from the temporary site, the state government has set aside 100 hectares of land for the permanent site in Kaltungo to enable the smooth take-off of the institution in the next academic session. He assured the committee that his administration will give them all the necessary support they need for the smooth discharge of their duties in the state. Earlier, the leader of the delegation and Executive Secretary of the National Board for Technical Education (NBTE), DrMas’udAdamuKazaure, said the committee constituted by the Minister of Education, Malam AdamuAdamu, was in the state to assess the site provided by the state government. He said the committee will put in place all the mechanical works needed for the flagging-off and commencement of academic activities at the polytechnic. Kazaure said the academic programmes of the school will be tailored towards the need of the state.  Gombe approves take-off site for Federal Polytechnic Kaltungo FG confirms Lokoja as varsity site Okorocha sets up governing councils for new tertiary institutions OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY